dcterms:description: The MNIST dataset contains images of handwritten digits. In this study, the authors used the digits 0 and 8, randomly selecting 5000 samples for training and testing.
dcterms:title: MNIST

dcterms:creator: Ken Lang
dcterms:description: The NEWS20 dataset is a collection of newsgroup documents. In this study, documents belonging to the topic 'sci' were taken as positive samples, while those in the topic 'talk' were taken as negative samples.
dcterms:title: NEWS20

dcterms:description: The RUIJIN dataset contains over ten thousand diabetes records collected from various branches of the Shanghai Ruijin Hospital. It includes demographic, lifestyle, and medical information relevant for diabetes prediction.
dcterms:title: RUIJIN
